Sentencas: Development of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode with high resistance to coking and sulfur poisoning is highly desirable for the direct application of natural gas in SOFC.
Titulo: Improving electrochemical performance of (Cu, Sm)CeO2 anode with anchored Cu nanoparticles for direct utilization of natural gas in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, a (Cu, Sm)CeO2 anode with anchored Cu nanoparticles has been prepared.
Titulo: Improving electrochemical performance of (Cu, Sm)CeO2 anode with anchored Cu nanoparticles for direct utilization of natural gas in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Most of Cu nanoparticles particle size ranges from 20 to 50 nm, which can increase the conductivity and catalytic activity of the anode.
Titulo: Improving electrochemical performance of (Cu, Sm)CeO2 anode with anchored Cu nanoparticles for direct utilization of natural gas in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Cu/CSCO10 supported cell exhibits a maximum power density of 404.6 mW/cm(2) at 600 degrees C when dry methane is used as fuel while its ohmic resistance is only 0.39 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Improving electrochemical performance of (Cu, Sm)CeO2 anode with anchored Cu nanoparticles for direct utilization of natural gas in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single SOFC shows good stability when H2S content in the fuel is less than 150 ppm.
Titulo: Improving electrochemical performance of (Cu, Sm)CeO2 anode with anchored Cu nanoparticles for direct utilization of natural gas in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Up to 900 h of continuous stable operation with simulated natural gas and commercial natural gas as fuel prove the advantages and application potential of this anode.
Titulo: Improving electrochemical performance of (Cu, Sm)CeO2 anode with anchored Cu nanoparticles for direct utilization of natural gas in solid oxide fuel cells
